						<summary>

						<p>This belongs to the reign of Parakēsarivarman ‘who took the head of the Pāṇḍya’, and records the gift of a quarter (<hi rend="italic">vēli</hi>) of land for the maintenance of a garden by one Tiruveṇkāṭṭu-Pichchaṉ named Parāntaka Mūvēndevēḷār, who also figures in No. 260 of 1907 ascribed to the reign of Parāntaka II Sundara-Chōḷa, where he is said to have endowed a flower garden to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
